<title>INDIA: India court adjourns Enron case to May 2.</title>
<headline>India court adjourns Enron case to May 2.</headline>
<dateline>NEW DELHI 1996-04-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>India's Supreme Court on Monday adjourned till next month a hearing on a petition that seeks to halt a $2.3 billion power project being built by a subsidiary of U.S.-based Enron Corp.</p>
<p>The court asked the Centre for Indian Trade Union, which filed a plea challenging the project's approval by the Central Electricity Authority, to prove that it genuinely represented a public cause in a hearing scheduled for May 2.</p>
<p>The trade union body appealed to the Supreme Court after the Bombay High Court dismissed a lawsuit against the Dabhol Power Company in December. The power project is being built in the western state of Maharashtra, of which Bombay is the capital.</p>
